                      <div>minecraft:behavior.follow_owner (4)</div>
                      <div>minecraft:behavior.sit (5)</div>
                      <div>minecraft:behavior.random_stroll (6)</div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </CardContent>
            </Card>
          </div>

          <Card>
            <CardHeader>
              <CardTitle>AI Behavior Best Practices</CardTitle>
              <CardDescription>Guidelines for creating effective entity AI</CardDescription>
            </CardHeader>
            <CardContent>
              <div className="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
                <div>
                  <h5 className="font-medium text-green-600 dark:text-green-400 mb-3">âœ… Do</h5>
                  <ul className="text-sm space-y-2">
                    <li>â€¢ Always include minecraft:behavior.float as priority 0</li>
                    <li>â€¢ Use priority gaps to allow inserting behaviors later</li>
                    <li>â€¢ Test behavior conflicts thoroughly</li>
                    <li>â€¢ Group related behaviors with similar priorities</li>
                    <li>â€¢ Use component groups for different AI states</li>
                    <li>â€¢ Include panic behavior for non-combat entities</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>

                <div>
                  <h5 className="font-medium text-red-600 dark:text-red-400 mb-3">âŒ Don't</h5>
                  <ul className="text-sm space-y-2">
                    <li>â€¢ Skip the float behavior (entities will drown)</li>
                    <li>â€¢ Use the same priority for multiple behaviors</li>
                    <li>â€¢ Create circular behavior dependencies</li>
                    <li>â€¢ Overcomplicate simple entities</li>
                    <li>â€¢ Forget to test edge cases</li>
                    <li>â€¢ Ignore performance implications of complex AI</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>
              </div>
            </CardContent>
          </Card>
        </TabsContent>
      </Tabs>
    </section>
  );
}

